libbrahe
------------------------------------------

Brahe is where I put all sorts of useful mathematic functions that don't seem
to fit anywhere else. Among the bits and pieces here, you'll find:

 * A function, brahe_sigdig, that rounds floating-point values to a specific
   number of significant digits -- very useful in scientific and engineering
   applications.
 * Several pseudorandom number generators, including the Marsenne Twister,
   various algorithms by Marsaglia, and ISAAC.
 * Least common multiple and greatest common denominator functions.
 * A few trigonometry functions for finding the inversions of hyperbolic sine,
   cosine, and tangent.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.2-1
  libbrahe1.3_3-1.3.2-1bl2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/libbrahe

Canonical download:
  mirror://debian/pool/main/libb/libbrahe/libbrahe_1.3.2.orig.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libbrahe-1.3.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libbrahe-1.3.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libbrahe-1.3.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbrahe-1.3.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbrahe1.3_3-1.3.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbrahe-devel-1.3.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libbrahe)
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_fft.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_gcflcm.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_pretty.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_prng.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_rounding.exe
  /usr/bin/brahe_test_trig.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libbrahe.README
  /usr/share/doc/libbrahe/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libbrahe/LicenseClosedSource.txt
  /usr/share/doc/libbrahe/LicenseOpenSource.txt

(libbrahe1.3_3)
  /usr/bin/cygbrahe-1-3-3.dll

(libbrahe-devel)
  /usr/include/libbrahe/mathtools.h
  /usr/include/libbrahe/prng.h
  /usr/lib/libbrahe.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libbrahe.pc

